The paper deals with secure communication in a Multiple-Access-Channel (MAC) and proposes a novel secure coding scheme. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of tools from number theory to analyze the probability of error, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
